articles.description: Matt Mobley scored 26 points and grabbed a key rebound with 4.2 seconds left, and St. Bonaventure beat Rhode Island 77-74 to snap the 16th-ranked Rams' 16-game winning streak on Friday night.
articles.headline: St. Bonaventure upsets No. 16 Rhode Island with 77-74 win

images.caption: Bonnies big man LaDarien Griffin slams home the go-ahead bucket and Rhode Island's Jared Terrell's three is no good as the St. Bonaventure student section storms the court.
images.name: St. Bonaventure knocks off No. 16 Rhode Island in dramatic fashion

articles.description: James Towns scored 20 points, Kahlil Dukes added 17 and the pair fueled a second-half rally after Niagara lost high-scoring guard Matt Scott to edge Iona 85-84 on Friday night in a meeting of the third- and fourth-place teams in the Metro Atlantic...
articles.headline: Niagara overcomes loss of Scott in 85-84 win over Iona

articles.description: No. 21 Texas A&M responded to its return to the Top 25 by losing at Missouri on Wednesday and now the Aggies likely must win at Arkansas on Saturday to remain in the rankings.
articles.headline: No. 21 Texas A&M faces tough test at Arkansas

articles.description: Kameron Chatman had his ninth double-double of the season with 26 points and 11 rebounds to help Detroit Mercy beat Youngstown State 94-84 on Friday night.
articles.headline: Detroit Mercy outlasts Youngstown State 94-84
